      • transfer

        public SBMLDocument transfer​(SBMLDocument sbmlDocument,
                             java.lang.String[] keys)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Transfers information from the Cobra style notes of species and reactions to the annotations (see example below). 
         Example:
 
 Cobra style note of a species:
  <notes>
    <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p>KEGG Compound: C00004</p>
    </body>
  </notes>
         
 New annotation of the species (after the transfer of the information):
   <annotation>
     <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
       <rdf:Description rdf:about="#cfa155dc-e6ed-4d90-8b0b-ad4cb8a88d6b">
         <bqbiol:is>
           <rdf:Bag>
             <rdf:li rdf:resource="http://identifiers.org/kegg.compound/C00004" />
           </rdf:Bag>
         </bqbiol:is>
       </rdf:Description>
     </rdf:RDF>
   </annotation>
        Parameters:
        sbmlDocument - the SBMLDocument where the information should be transfered from the notes
        keys - a string array with the keys from the elements of the notes that should be transfered
        Returns:
        the new SBMLDocument with transfered information in the annotations
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an error occurs
